    <stitle>INSTRUMENTS - TACHOMETER - OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>OPERATION</title>
        <para>The sensor is a magnetic pickup that senses the rotation of the flywheel ring gear on the engine. The
            sensor's permanent magnet establishes a magnetic field at the tip of the sensor,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0803413">Figure 13</hotlnk>
            . This magnetic field is interrupted regularly by the flywheel ring gear teeth. This interruption creates
            voltage impulses that are transmitted to the tachometer head through the microprocessor in the cluster.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0803413" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0803413" filename="../figg08/g0803413.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Sensor Adjustment - Tachometer</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SENSOR BODY</callout1>
                <callout1>2. LOCKNUT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FLYWHEEL HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SENSOR CONNECTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>5. FLYWHEEL RING GEAR</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
